  "texts": [
    "The fine-tuned version outperformed the pretrained version across all five recorded metrics, see Figure 4.",
    "In the figure, rouge1 and rouge2 measure the overlap of unigrams and bigrams, respectively, capturing basic content and phrase-level fluency.",
    "rougeL evaluates the longest common subsequence between generated and reference summaries, reflecting sentence-level structure.",
    "We also report rougeLsum as an aggregate score that combines the individual ROUGE metrics to provide an overall measure of summarization quality.",
    "The results suggest that fine-tuning a closed-source LLM can lead to quantitative improvements in ChronoLLM performance."
  ],
